2. Differences between Flask and Django
    Feature	  Flask	Django
    Type	Micro-framework	Full-stack framework
    Flexibility	Very high	Moderate
    Built-in features	Minimal	Batteries included
    ORM	Optional	Built-in
    Learning curve	Easy	Steeper
    Use case	APIs, small apps	Large applications
    Real-world analogy
    Flask → Like LEGO blocks → build everything yourself
    Django → Like a ready-made car → comes with engine, seats, etc.
    Example
    Flask: simple API for a startup MVP
    Django: full-scale system like an admin dashboard or social platform
