5. How do you structure a FastAPI application for production use?
Recommended structure
    app/
    │
    ├── main.py
    ├── database.py
    ├── models/
    │   └── user.py
    ├── schemas/
    │   └── user.py
    ├── routes/
    │   └── user.py
    ├── services/
    │   └── user_service.py
    ├── core/
    │   └── config.py

Example breakdown
    routes/user.py
    from fastapi import APIRouter

    router = APIRouter()

    @router.get("/users")
    def get_users():
        return [{"name": "John"}]
    main.py

    from fastapi import FastAPI
    from routes import user

    app = FastAPI()

    app.include_router(user.router)
    Best practices (real-world production)

    ✅ Use environment variables
    ✅ Use async DB (asyncpg) for performance
    ✅ Add authentication (JWT/OAuth)
    ✅ Logging & monitoring
    ✅ Use Docker
